name Spiced Pear Chutney
serves 1
tags preserve, autumn

- 1 kg pears
- 1 "tart apple"
Wash, core and cut into small pieces.
-> fruit

- 2 onions
- 2 cloves garlic
@nodep
Peel and finely dice.
-> onions and garlic

- 50 g ginger
@nodep
Peel and finely chop.
-> ginger

- 1 "unwaxed lemon"
@nodep
Wash in hot water, dry, zest and juice.
-> lemon zest and juice

- 150 g raisins
- 1 "chilli"
- 0.5 tsp chilli flakes
- 2 cloves
- 1 tsp mustard seeds
- 2 sprigs thyme
- 1 tsp salt
- 300 ml "tarragon or white wine vinegar"
- 250 g "brown sugar"
= fruit
= onions and garlic
= ginger
= lemon zest and juice
Combine all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Simmer uncovered over medium
heat for about 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Fill into jars immediately while hot and seal well.
